<TITLE> Lightning, storm kill 4 in Pabna, Magura </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 4 (bdnews24.com) - Lightning killed three of a family in Shakpala village under Faridpur Upazila in Pabna Thursday night. Meanwhile, a seven-year-old boy died in Moghi village under Sadar Upazila in Magura after he was crushed under the wall of his home during a storm. The bdnews24.com Pabna Correspondent reports: Shah Alam ,40, his wife Rokeya Khatun, 35, and mother-in-law Achhiya Khatun, 60, died shortly after the lightning struck their home at 11.30pm. Pabna district police chief AFM Masum Rabbani said that the thunderstorm swept through the district, damaging up to 300 thatched homes. The bdnews24.com Magura correspondent reports: A wall collapse killed Shwadhin,7, during the storm. Over 500 homes were damaged by the storm in the area. bdnews2
